review_blob: Bottle. Looks nice in the glass with a pleasant aroma that is slightly sweet. Smooth on the tongue  with citrus undertones. Refreshing. Overall, pretty decent for the style.

Bards Gold is the beer I tried. Bottle. 

This is a horrible beer. I wasnt expecting much given that it is a sorghum beer, but this was just bad. Looks decent enough in the glass, but plug your nose if you take a sip. 

Id rather choke down Colt 45 from a can than experience Bards gold again.

Can. Pale color with thin head. Looks nice and refreshing in the glass. Malty flavor with very faint hops. Quite different from most of Surlys beers. 

Not bad. Wont mind finishing of the last 3 of my 4 pack.

Looked nice in the glass but that was about the only good part of my experience drinking this beer. I personally could not smell or taste any blackberry on this beer. Perhaps it was a bad bottle or something as usually I can pick up the berry stuff. Tasted okay but nothing great. 

Overall, disappointing -- like most Sam Adams beer Ive tried.

On tap. Not as much aroma as I expected. Pours a light copper with a nice thick head. Hops is definitely present though not overwhelming. Very smooth going down and really quite tasty. I will be drinking this again. 

While this is labeled called a "red," it is not what I expect with a typical amber ale as designated. WIth its strong hop character, it much closer to an IPA.
Had on tap at brewery. Dark maroon color with decent head. Malty flavor with hints of spices. I would drink it again.

Beautiful pour with solid white head and faintly copper body. Aroma is enticing with hints of citrus. Can definitely taste the hops but they are not overwhelming. Crisp flavor with subtle sweetness always leaves me wanting more. This is an outstanding beer.
Pours a deep copper with a modest head. Aroma is fainter than Id expect considering the taste. This beer bursts with flavor and while it is quite hoppy, there is not excessive bitterness.

Beautiful in the glass with a faintly orange body and thin, white head. Aroma is intriguing and pulls you in - probably my favorite part of this beer. Definitely inspired by the Belgian White style, but much stronger in alcohol and more forceful in flavor. Enjoyed it greatly and still have one bottle left to relish.
Golden pour with a decent head. Nice flavor though seemed a little light on the hops. Refreshing and crisp.
beer_name: Big Sky Scape Goat Pale Ale

review_blob: Nonexistent aroma and flavor. I do drink  the High Life from time to time....when its this or water....though I think water out of the tap has more hops and malty character.
A nice backup when other brews arent available. Looks good in a glass and has a nice balance of hops. Really a very tasty beer.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Local beer for me. Pours a golden straw color with thin head. Watery feel on the tongue and theres really not much flavor for a wheat beer. Probably better than 15th percentile, but not much.
As far as tasteless and boring beer goes, this brew is a prime example. It might be decent as a chaser to a swig of whiskey, but beyond that, I cant imagine a reason to drink this.

An excellent brew. Deep brown appearance with a modest head that releases faint malt and nut aromas. Fairy light on the palate, but taste is excellent with nutty flavor and hints of roasty aftertaste.
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Okay appearance and aroma but flavor is a little overwhelming for me. A bit of malt flaver but mostly I was sensing alcohol on the tongue. Not terrible, but not my favorite.

This is a hometown beer for me so it is usually fresh and I generally drink it on tap if nothing more interesting is available. Aroma and appearance are standard for the style with a thin head and modest citrus on the nose. You can taste the hops but there is no overwhelming bitterness. Really a rather tasty and refreshing brew.

Draft. This is an excellent beer. Pours deep brown with minimal head. Aroma and body are fairly good. Taste is outstanding. A toasted nut flavor with hints of sweet molasses are found in this marvelous brew. Hops are balanced very nicely and do not overwhelm. I wish I could get this at home.

Bottle. Loved it. Aroma is crisp with hints of citrus. Appearance in the glass finds a classically cloudy gold body with a good head. Refreshing on the palate and quite flavorful without the spices overwhelming things. I already bought a second 6-pack.

Bottle. I love the name and the label. The beer itself has mild aroma with faint notes of coffee. Minimal head. Body is rather thin on the palate for a stout (even a sweet stout) but the flavor is quite good and surprisingly refreshing with roasted flavors not overpowering.
UPDATED: FEB 2, 2009
UPDATED: SEP 8, 2008
Pale color with modest head. Decent pilsner overall. A little bitter going down but still refreshing.

Massive carbonation. Perhaps I had a bad batch, but the fizzing was overwhelming as I could neither pour it to a glass or take a sip from the bottle. Cant even say I really tasted the beer as there was so much carbonation.

Some tough critics out there. I actually found this beer to be rather satisfying. Wonderful malt flavor with hints of caramel. Smooth going down and left me wanting another. One of the better brown ales Ive had recently.
Cant say I enjoyed this one. A little musty out of the bottle so maybe it would be better off the tap and closer to its home.
Overall quite a nice brew. Sweet, but not over the top. Thick, creamy taste and feel with a pleasant, roasted finish. I look forward to drinking the rest of the 6-pack.
